## 3. Runtime Execution Sequence Diagram (Artifact 5)

```plantuml
@startuml
skinparam participant {
  BackgroundColor White
  BorderColor Black
  ArrowColor Black
}
skinparam actor {
  BackgroundColor White
  BorderColor Black
}
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor Black
  ActorBorderColor Black
  LifeLineBorderColor Black
  LifeLineBackgroundColor White
}
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Courier"

actor User
participant "Camera Hardware" as Cam
participant "MediaPipe Detector" as MP
participant "Preprocessing Core" as Norm
database "Sliding Buffer (deque)" as Buff
participant "TFLite Interpreter (Flex)" as TF
participant "Arabic Rendering Core" as Rent
participant "PyQt5 HUD Display" as Display

User -> Cam : Perform sign gesture in camera view
activate Cam
Cam -> Cam : Resize raw frame to 320x240
Cam -> MP : Process Frame RGB
activate MP
MP -> Norm : Raw landmarks array (126-dim)
activate Norm
Norm -> Norm : Translate & Scale normalization (preprocessing.py)
Norm -> Buff : Append normalized feature vector
deactivate Norm
deactivate MP

alt Buffer size == 20 AND frame_idx % 3 == 0
  Buff -> TF : Set input tensor [1, 20, 126]
  activate TF
  TF -> TF : invoke()
  TF -> Rent : Softmax output class index & confidence
  deactivate TF
  activate Rent
  Rent -> Rent : Shape Arabic letters (arabic_reshaper)
  Rent -> Rent : Set layout right-to-left (python-bidi)
  Rent -> Display : Draw reshaped Arabic text glyphs
  deactivate Rent
else Buffer is filling / deque is not full
  Rent -> Display : Draw "Listening..." status overlay
end

Display -> User : Video output frame rendered on GUI
deactivate Cam
@enduml
```
